{"word":"αἶνος","slug":"αἶνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἶνος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <a href='S:αἰνέω'><el>αἰνέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>= <a href='S:μῦθος'><el>μῦθος</el></a>, <i>a tale, story</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>αἰνεῖν αἶνον</el> to tell <i>a tale</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: generally, <i>a saying, proverb</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= attic <el>ἔπαινος</el>, <i>praise</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}